# Cursor MCP ‚Äî canonical fix (remember forever)

**When Cursor MCP fails** (e.g. `bored` won‚Äôt connect, `MCP_CLIENT_ID required when OIDC_TOKEN_URL is set`, tools missing after spawn):

1. **Make Cursor match Claude Code.** Copy **`mcpServers`** from **`~/.claude.json`** into **`~/.cursor/mcp.json`** wholesale (same `command` / `args` / `env` per server). Add **`"type": "stdio"`** on each server if Claude omits it. **Do not** hand-merge one field at a time ‚Äî that recreated the broken state.

2. **OAuth must arrive atomically for `bored-mcp`.** **`OIDC_TOKEN_URL`, `MCP_CLIENT_ID`, `MCP_CLIENT_SECRET`, `MCP_SCOPE`, `BORED_API_URL`** must all be present together in **`env`** (Claude‚Äôs layout), **or** all come from a single **`envFile`** Cursor reliably loads ‚Äî **never** only token URL in inline `env` while client id lives only in `envFile` (Cursor merge order caused **`NotPresent`** + panic).

3. **`command`:** Use an **absolute path** to **`bored-mcp`** (release binary path). Don‚Äôt rely on **`${userHome}`** in `command` unless you‚Äôve confirmed Cursor expands it.

4. **Secrets:** If **`~/.cursor/mcp.json`** holds tokens ‚Üí **`chmod 600`**. Never paste those values into chat.

5. **One reload boundary:** After changing MCP JSON, tell the user **once** whether **MCP reload** vs **full quit Cursor** is needed; batch edits so they aren‚Äôt restart-looping for the same incident.

**Other machines / other clones:** Sync **`~/.cursor/rules/`** (this file) + **`~/.cursor/mcp.json`** via dotfiles or manual copy. The **`bored`** repo also ships the same rule at **`.cursor/rules/mcp-restart-discipline.mdc`** so any clone gets MCP discipline before dotfiles exist.

